s.com/1995-03-14/sports/sp-42741_1_andre-agassi?pg=1", "accessdate": "15 May 2010", "newspaper": "The Los Angeles Times", "first": "Bill", "last": "Dwyre"} He is the first man to win grand slams on all modern surfaces (previous holders of all grand slam tournaments played in an era of grass and clay only), and is regarded by a number of critics and fellow players to be among the greatest players of all time.{"citetype": "news", "title": "CBC Sports: &quot;Tennis's love affair with Agassi comes to an end&quot;", "url": "http://www.cbc.ca/sports/columns/newsmakers/andre-agassi.html", "urlstatus": "dead", "publisher": "Cbc.ca", "archiveurl": "https://web.archive.org/web/20130308123815/http://www.cbc.ca/sports/columns/newsmakers/andre-agassi.html", "archivedate": "8 March 2013", "accessdate": "15 May 2013", "last": "Molinaro", "first": "John"}{"citetype": "news", "date": "26 June 2002", "title": "Grand-slammed", "url": "https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/tennis/wimbledon/3030108/Grand-slammed.html", "work": "The Daily Telegraph", "location": "London", "accessdate": "6 May 2012", "first": "John", "last": "Parsons"}{"citetype": "news", "date": "4 September 2006", "title": "Stars pay tribute to Agassi", "url": "http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/tennis/5113548.stm", "work": "BBC Sport", "accessdate": "6 May 2012"} Both Rod Laver and Ken Rosewall also won major Pro Slam tournaments on all three surfaces (grass, clay, hard court) Rosewall in 1963 and Laver in 1967.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://bleacherreport.com/articles/213115-dispelling-the-myths-of-rocket-rod-laver", "title": "Dispelling the Myths of &quot;Rocket&quot; Rod Laver", "date": "6 July 2009", "website": "bleacherreport.com", "publisher": "Bleacher Report, Inc.", "accessdate": "5 September 2018", "last1": "Zikov", "first1": "Sergey"}
